dismissalText.commentary: Chamara Silva b Starc 33 (72b 2x4 0x6 105m) SR: 45.83

dismissalComment.html: Starc has three! And two of them from batsmen playing on! Silva has tried to drive through off, almost down on one knee as he plays it, he hasn't judged the angle quite right and a thick inside edge crashes into the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Upul Tharanga lbw b Watson 28 (53b 3x4 0x6 64m) SR: 52.83

dismissalComment.html: Watson makes the breakthrough! He's swung it in to Tharanga, who pushed forward without much intent, the ball struck him in line and Erasmus says that's out. Pitched in line, straightened well and the only question was height, but it looked good at first glance.

headshotImage.caption: Clinton McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Clinton McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: gone! McKay makes the breakthrough, it was on the pads, Dilshan tried to flick it through square leg but only succeeded in lofting it to Hussey, who was in the circle between midwicket and square leg
two in the over for McKay! This one seams away as well, but started outside off stump and the width enticed Sangakkara to slash at that one, a thin little edge is taken by Haddin

McKay gets his third! Very sharp catch by Cameron White at second slip as Jayawardene drives hard at a ball on a good length outside off, there might have been a little seam movement away and it flew off a thick edge high to White's right

good catch from Smith! Perera threw everything at that one to a fuller ball, it's flown off a leading edge towards point, Smith looks to chase it back behind square but then has to adjust his movement, and takes it well above his head, facing back towards third man. That was not an easy catch, but Smith made it look pretty comfortable in the end.

headshotImage.caption: Suraj Randiv player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Suraj Randiv player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: McKay has five! That's what the Aussies need to do against the tail - aim at the stumps! Randiv was backing off and opening the shoulders, he missed and McKay hit the off stump

headshotImage.caption: Angelo Mathews, player page headshot cutout 2023

dismissalComment.html: got him! Starc is ecstatic as he collects his first ODI wicket! Angled across Mathews, who was on the move and trying to drive through off, a thick inside edge rockets back onto the leg stump

gone! Starc gets his second with another ball that bounces sharply off a good length, Mendis has just tried to defend that ball and a thick edge is taken at chest height by Haddin, very good bowling from Starc

headshotImage.caption: Chamara Silva player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Chamara Silva player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Starc has three! And two of them from batsmen playing on! Silva has tried to drive through off, almost down on one knee as he plays it, he hasn't judged the angle quite right and a thick inside edge crashes into the stumps
It's all over for Sri Lanka, Starc finishes with four as Malinga pulls over midwicket but gets it high off the bat, Ferguson at deep midwicket gets underneath that and has no trouble taking the catch

commentTextItems.html: there's the winning runs! Clarke waits on this and guides it off the face of the bat to third man, the umpire signals four, so he also brings up his half-century

commentPostTextItems.html: Australia have won by eight wickets - a consolation victory, and Sri Lanka take the series 2-1. Clint McKay is Man of the Match and the Player of the Series is Lasith Malinga.
Well played by Michael Clarke to guide that chase, but the win was set up by superb bowling from Clint McKay and Mitchell Starc, who showed some real promise in his second ODI.

Peter English is at the Gabba and has sent through his bulletin super quickly. Here it is. So, well done to Australia, but extra well done to Sri Lanka over the course of their tour. Meanwhile, check out the scores in Ahmedabad, where New Zealand are really challenging India in the first Test!
From me, Brydon Coverdale, thanks for joining us throughout the series, and goodbye for now.

commentTextItems.html: on the move, Clarke drives to point
drives to cover, can't beat the field

commentPreTextItems.html: So, one run needed and Clarke is on 46. Can he get it to the boundary to reach his half-century?

commentTextItems.html: pushed to point, no run there

dismissalComment.html: got him! Starc is ecstatic as he collects his first ODI wicket! Angled across Mathews, who was on the move and trying to drive through off, a thick inside edge rockets back onto the leg stump

dismissalText.commentary: Jeevan Mendis c Haddin b Starc 5 (11b 0x4 0x6 18m) SR: 45.45

dismissalComment.html: gone! Starc gets his second with another ball that bounces sharply off a good length, Mendis has just tried to defend that ball and a thick edge is taken at chest height by Haddin, very good bowling from Starc

headshotImage.caption: Chamara Silva player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Chamara Silva player page headshot cutout, 2021

headshotImage.caption: Chamara Silva player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Chamara Silva player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Chamara Silva b Starc 33 (72b 2x4 0x6 105m) SR: 45.83

dismissalComment.html: Starc has three! And two of them from batsmen playing on! Silva has tried to drive through off, almost down on one knee as he plays it, he hasn't judged the angle quite right and a thick inside edge crashes into the stumps

headshotImage.caption: Clinton McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Clinton McKay player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Thisara Perera c Smith b McKay 3 (7b 0x4 0x6 6m) SR: 42.85

dismissalComment.html: good catch from Smith! Perera threw everything at that one to a fuller ball, it's flown off a leading edge towards point, Smith looks to chase it back behind square but then has to adjust his movement, and takes it well above his head, facing back towards third man. That was not an easy catch, but Smith made it look pretty comfortable in the end.

dismissalText.commentary: Suraj Randiv b McKay 7 (9b 1x4 0x6 23m) SR: 77.77

dismissalComment.html: McKay has five! That's what the Aussies need to do against the tail - aim at the stumps! Randiv was backing off and opening the shoulders, he missed and McKay hit the off stump

headshotImage.caption: Callum Ferguson player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Callum Ferguson player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalText.commentary: Lasith Malinga c Ferguson b Starc 2 (9b 0x4 0x6 15m) SR: 22.22

dismissalComment.html: It's all over for Sri Lanka, Starc finishes with four as Malinga pulls over midwicket but gets it high off the bat, Ferguson at deep midwicket gets underneath that and has no trouble taking the catch

dismissalComment.html: Fernando strikes! Good ball at 150kph and cramped Watson a bit, he's tried to open the face and cut that to third man but it was too close, he's simply guided it to Mathews at first slip

dismissalText.commentary: Brad Haddin c & b Fernando 31 (44b 3x4 0x6 74m) SR: 70.45

dismissalComment.html: Haddin's on his way, Fernando gets a well deserved second wicket, it was a bouncer that got too high on Haddin, who pulled and the top edge flew high in the air, Fernando ran over to short midwicket to take the catch himself. And then threw the ball up and headed it away!
